President Donald Trump has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the 2018 PyeongChang Olympic Winter Games in South Korea. Vice President Mike Pence will lead the delegation, accompanied by Second Lady Karen Pence. Other members of the delegation include Chairman of the House Foreign Affairs Committee Ed Royce, Commander of United Nations Command Vincent K. Brooks, Former Commander of United Nations Command James D. Thurman, Chargé d’Affaires ad interim at the U.S. Embassy Seoul Marc E. Knapper, and 2002 Olympic Gold Medalist Sarah Hughes.